<h2>1. Business Information We Collect</h2>
<p>We collect information provided by your organization, including:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Company registration details (name, tax ID, business license)</li>
    <li>Administrator contact information</li>
    <li>Employee training records and participation data</li>
    <li>Billing and payment information</li>
    <li>Corporate learning content and materials</li>
</ul>

<h2>2. How We Use Business Data</h2>
<p>Your corporate data helps us:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Provide enterprise learning solutions</li>
    <li>Manage team training programs</li>
    <li>Generate organizational learning reports</li>
    <li>Invoice and process payments</li>
    <li>Comply with corporate service agreements</li>
</ul>

<h2>3. Data Sharing & Confidentiality</h2>
<p>We treat corporate data with strict confidentiality:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Employee data is only visible to authorized administrators</li>
    <li>Financial data is processed through secure payment gateways</li>
    <li>May share aggregated analytics (non-identifiable) for service improvement</li>
    <li>Disclose when required by commercial contracts or law</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Corporate Data Controls</h2>
<p>Your organization can:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Designate authorized administrators</li>
    <li>Set internal access permissions</li>
    <li>Export training completion records</li>
    <li>Request data processing agreements</li>
</ul>

<h2>5. Security Measures</h2>
<p>We implement enterprise-grade protections including:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Encrypted data transmission (TLS 1.2+)</li>
    <li>Regular security audits</li>
    <li>Role-based access controls</li>
    <li>SOC 2 compliant infrastructure</li>
</ul>

<h2>6. Policy Updates</h2>
<p>Will notify account administrators of material changes 30 days in advance.</p>

